===Justice, Peace and Creation Commission===
Justice, Peace and Creation has drawn many elements together with an [[environment (biophysical)|environmental]] focus. Its mandate is:

{{quote|To analyze and reflect on justice, peace and creation ''in their interrelatedness'', to promote values and practices that make for a culture of peace, and to work towards a culture of solidarity with young people, women, Indigenous Peoples and racially and ethnically oppressed people.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/index-e.html|title=World Council of Churches — World Council of Churches|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;}}

Focal issues have been [[globalization]] and the emergence of [[new social movements]] (in terms of people ''bonding together'' in the struggle for justice, peace, and the protection of creation).&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book
  | last = Schmitthenner
  | first = Ulrich
  | title = Contributions of churches and civil society to justice, peace and the integrity of creation: a compendium (with CD-ROM)
  | publisher = IKO
  | year = 1999
  | location = Frankfurt, Germany
  | isbn = 978-3-88939-491-0}}
&lt;/ref&gt;

Attention has been given to issues around:
*economy&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/economy.html|title=JPC Concerns - economy|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;
*environment&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/ecology.html|title=World Council of Churches — World Council of Churches|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;
*Indigenous Peoples&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/indig.html|title=World Council of Churches — World Council of Churches|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;
*peace&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/peace.html|title=JPC Concerns - Peace|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;
*people with disabilities&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/disabil.html World Council of Churches — World Council of Churches]. Wcc-coe.org (2013-08-04). Retrieved on 2013-08-09.&lt;/ref&gt;
*[[Programme to Combat Racism|racism]]&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/racism-e.html|title=World Council of Churches — World Council of Churches|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;
*women&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/jpc/women.html|title=World Council of Churches — World Council of Churches|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;
